Once you have Cody in your IDE, you can take advantage of its context-aware chat. Ask Cody to explain code, help you fix or debug code, or even write new code for you. When you talk to Cody, try giving specific instructions to craft the exact answer you’re looking for:

- How is this project organized? Describe the file structure.
- How would I write an API call to do X? Write an example API call for this.
- Rewrite this code to include error handling.

You can also follow up after Cody provides an answer to get more details or add further instructions.

